===Etymology===
Possibly derived from {{der|en|he|יָעֵל||tr=ya'el|mountain goat}}. Possibly from {{der|en|cy|iâl|t=clearing, glade}}. Compare {{cog|la|eale}}.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[mythical]] [[beast]] in [[European]] [[mythology]] and [[heraldry]], usually portrayed as an [[antelope]]- or [[goat]]-like four-legged creature with large [[horn]]s that it can swivel in any direction.
# A [[fertile]] [[upland]].
